==English==
===Adjective===
'''harder''' (Comparative adjective; Positive: [[hard]]; Superlative: [[hardest]])

#Comparative form of the adjective [[hard]].  More [[rigid]] or more [[difficult]].
#:''He is more likely to succeed because he tries '''harder'''.''
#:''Steel is '''harder''' than copper so we use steel tools to cut copper pipes.''

===Etymology 2===
{{D.}} ''harder'' / ''herder'': mullet.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
#(South African) Any of several species of [[mullet]] often used to make [[bokkom]]s.
